HEADWORD: Maravedi
<hw>Mar`a*ve"di</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Sp.
<ets>maraved⟦iacute⟧</ets>; -- so called from the
<ets>Mor⟦amac⟧bit⟦imac⟧n</ets> (lit., the steadfast), an Arabian dynasty
which reigned in Africa and Spain. Cf. <er>Marabout</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Numis.)</fld> <def>A small copper coin of Spain, equal to three
mils American money, less than a farthing sterling. Also, an ancient
Spanish gold coin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>maravilla</ent>⟦br⟧
